{"type":"message","id":"d4b97a16","parentId":"8cba921b","timestamp":"2026-06-09T07:29:21.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to restructure the SOP to make it a truly effective product selection process. Let me think about what needs to be done:\n\n1. Current SOP v6.0 has issues based on the June 7 data:\n   - Vietnam hair accessories market is in overall decline\n   - Price points are too low ($0.4-$2.0 range)\n   - Gross margins can't meet the 70% threshold\n   - No KOL promotion videos\n   - TikTok data granularity mismatch (weekly vs 24-hour data)\n\n2. The user wants a \"真正能选品的流程\" - a truly actionable product selection process\n\nLet me think about what a realistic SOP should look like:\n\n**Issues with current approach:**\n- The 70% gross margin requirement seems unrealistic for low-price items\n- Vietnam market has price ceiling issues\n- TikTok data (Sorftime) doesn't provide 24-hour granular data\n\n\n- The data source is Sorftime API → TikTok category report, not real-time TikTok Shop data\n\nI need to restructure with a clearer data source (Sorftime category_report or tiktok_product_trend), set more realistic margin thresholds based on price segments, add market-specific filters, and create an actionable workflow. Let me first check what data sources and capabilities I actually have access to through the Sorftime MCP, then build a practical SOP based on real API capabilities rather than theoretical requirements.\n\nFor a genuine product selection process, I should focus on what's actually viable: targeting $3-15 price range for better margins, being more flexible on margin requirements since anything under $3 makes it hard to be profitable, diversifying across both Vietnam and Thailand markets, and using Shopee as a validation layer instead of relying solely on TikTok data. The core workflow should move from trend spotting to Shopee validation to 1688 profitability check to Feishu documentation. Let me map out what the user actually needs and build a proper SOP around real API data and actionable thresholds. The core workflow should be scanning for products with strong indicators like high view-to-sale conversion and positive growth, then validating those candidates against Shopee and 1688 data, calculating actual profit margins, and finally filtering for IP risk before adding viable options to the spreadsheet. I should review the existing SOP documentation to understand the full scope before creating a comprehensive revision","thinkingSignature":"25675a363881b5f05076cfc027b25119a0cbb15dd15829415e208e40eb24c343"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好，我先把现有 SOP 和最近执行情况都看一遍，然后重写一个真正能用的。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_19f65cd5f47a484397b816a3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/workspace-tts/docs/SOP-v6.0.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58590,"output":533,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59123,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780966266006,"responseId":"0676967a5566f3d9d0556b22be989f18"}}
