{"type":"message","id":"27b3ba6e","parentId":"f601c9e5","timestamp":"2026-06-09T07:29:21.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze what's actually usable vs what's in the SOP:\n\n**What the SOP claims vs what's actually available:**\n\n1. `tiktok_product_trend` - takes a productId, not a category/keyword scan. There's no \"batch scan\" for TikTok products. The SOP assumes there's a批量接口 but there isn't.\n\n2. `tiktok_similar_product` - searches similar products by name, returns 20 per page. This is the actual TikTok search tool.\n\n3. `shopee_product_search` - searches Shopee products with filters (nodeId, price, month sales, etc.) - this is actually useful and has good filters.\n\n\n4. `ali1688_similar_product` - finds 1688 sourcing for products by name.\n\n5. `tiktok_category_report` - returns category-level data (Top products in a category).\n\n6. `tiktok_product_detail` - gets product details by ID.\n\nThe core issue is that `tiktok_product_trend` requires product IDs upfront, and there are no tools for directly accessing TikTok's search rankings or store listings. So the SOP's Phase 1 scanning approach isn't really feasible with these tools.\n\nThe actual viable path forward is using `shopee_product_search` to identify trending products through filters, then cross-referencing with `tiktok_similar_product` to validate on TikTok, using `tiktok_category_report` for category-level insights, and `ali1688_similar_product` for profit calculations. There's also a critical data quality issue—the SOP mentions 24-hour sales growth and KOL video data for Vietnam, but the logs show these don't actually exist or return empty. And the 70% margin requirement might be unrealistic when working with the actual tool constraints.\n\nNow I'm working through the real math on pricing. If a product costs ¥5 on 1688 and I want a 70% gross margin on TikTok VN, I need to work backward from the formula: after accounting for the ~45% in platform fees and logistics, the TikTok selling price needs to be at least ¥16 to maintain that margin on a ¥5 cost product. Converting to Vietnamese Dong, that's roughly 54,000 VND minimum, which aligns with the SOP's price floor for hair clips. But here's the tension—if I'm targeting the higher margin requirement, the prices I'm seeing in the actual market (9,000-49,000 VND range) fall well below what's needed to make the math work.\n\nThe real issue is that my tools aren't giving me access to the raw ingredients I need. I'm working with incomplete data on what's actually available to source, so I need to build a practical sourcing workflow that works with these constraints rather than fighting against them.\n\nThe approach is to start with what I can actually get—use the category reports from Shopee and TikTok to identify what's trending, then validate those products through the similarity search APIs, calculate whether the margins make sense at the price points I can achieve, and only proceed if the numbers work out. Let me document this into a real SOP","thinkingSignature":"bda9901b21fdb958a25150f68dfd547eb902c5d220b6b856792a1b245a32e02f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n情况很清楚了。现有 SOP 有一个致命问题：**它假设有批量 TikTok 扫描接口，但实际工具没有**。`tiktok_product_trend` 要的是 productId，没有批量搜索 TikTok 潜力产品的入口。\n\n实际能用的是：\n- `tiktok_category_report` → 类目 Top 产品\n- `tiktok_similar_product` → 关键词搜相似\n- `shopee_product_search` → Shopee 筛选搜索（最实用）\n- `ali1688_similar_product` → 1688 找货源\n\n我来重写一个真正能落地的 SOP："}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3627,"output":756,"cacheRead":60216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64599,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780966306433,"responseId":"067696a3d5eaaf0ac9b0c281f04f45d6"}}
