{"type":"message","id":"64fd5c27","parentId":"eeb4c60b","timestamp":"2026-06-09T07:29:21.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The patch needs to be a proper object, not a JSON string. Let me try using the edit tool approach differently - or use a proper patch format. Actually, looking at the cron schema more carefully, the `patch` should be an object (not a string), and the fields should be at the top level of the patch object, not nested inside. Let me try the correct format.\n\nActually the issue is the JSON string I passed was escaped. Let me use the exec tool to directly call the cron API in a different way.\n\nActually, looking at the cron schema again, the patch format should be the same as the job object but only partial. Let me just delete and recreate the job instead.","thinkingSignature":"75c17f35d17e87abc082861ca8d32fc88d9719a9ec5b338debd9dbdd6f6c5f30"},{"type":"text","text":"格式问题，我删掉重建：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_je6mcr2w2nnn_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"remove","jobId":"5c75bbb4-b1c3-446b-bde9-74bed5a396c6"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94103,"output":208,"cacheRead":54174,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148485,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780989625949,"responseId":"0676f1bae19f9c88f82d6791260c2628"}}
