{"type":"message","id":"4fb1a55f","parentId":"2685702d","timestamp":"2026-06-09T07:30:14.031Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see two important things:\n\n1. The Vietnam v7.0 cron **failed** with \"Context overflow: prompt too large for the model\". This means the cron ran out of context because the payload is too large. I need to fix this.\n\n2. The Thailand v7.0 cron is still in queued state (nextRunAtMs is set but no lastRunAtMs).\n\nFor the Vietnam cron failure - \"Context overflow\" - this is because the payload message is too long for the model to handle in one prompt. The cron isolated session has a context limit and my v7.0 payload message is too verbose.\n\n\nThe solution is to trim down the payload messages significantly and disable both crons for now until I can fix them properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"d46fdeb85b9ea2983e2cf08708fbfa5e26ecebd9dfddc2ddf7847918a96b02b3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n发现两个关键问题：\n\n1. **越南 v7.0 cron 失败了**——`Context overflow: prompt too large`，我的 payload 消息太长（v7.0 写得太啰嗦），模型上下文装不下\n2. **两个 cron 都在跑发饰**，但我们已经确认要换类目了\n\n先把两个 cron 暂停，等 SOP 改完再重开：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b7d76f273772407287155ec2","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"update","jobId":"6ee6a981-7b1c-4560-a848-139401e7bfa6","patch":{"enabled":false}}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3ae2838a33d4423aaa996ef1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"update","jobId":"dde46f87-45b0-4c74-bad0-88c500754a92","patch":{"enabled":false}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2304,"output":370,"cacheRead":94592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97266,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780990208729,"responseId":"0676f401ac31b6e62d4cb9da19b6dce5"}}
